  "explanation": "Embezzlement constitutes a serious breach of fiduciary duty and trust placed in the defendant by their employer. However, the court must weigh several mitigating factors. The defendant has no prior criminal record, indicating this is an isolated lapse in judgment rather than a pattern of criminal behavior. Furthermore, the defendant has already made efforts to partially repay the embezzled funds of $25,000, showing remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. To balance the need for deterrence and punishment with the opportunity for rehabilitation and complete restitution, a short term of incarceration is deemed appropriate.",
